As a JIRA user, it would be really helpful to edit attachments on the fly.

h4. +Current scenario:+
To edit an attachment in JIRA, an user needs to manually download the attachment. Then edit what is needed, save, and upload a new attachment (and then remove the old one if necessary).

h4. +Suggestion:+
# When the user clicks a link to a document it downloads it and opens it (Word/Excel etc);
# The document is locked for concurrent editing;
# When the document is closed, JIRA checks if it has been edited, and if so displays a box asking if you wish to upload the change and write a comment.

h5. +Notes:+ 
A similar thing can be achieved in Confluence with the [GoEdit|https://marketplace.atlassian.com/plugins/de.kontextwork.goedit] add-on. This is also tracked for Confluence on [CONF-5932|https://jira.atlassian.com/browse/CONF-5932].

