The [Adding custom fields to email|https://developer.atlassian.com/display/JIRADEV/Adding+Custom+Fields+to+Email] page from DAC mentions that the user can discover the customfield ID by looking into it in the database, but it doesn't provide the query anywhere, so I edited to page to add the query after the first step. Here is my modification:

{quote}
If you want to find this via database, just run the following query:

{code:sql}
SELECT * FROM customfield WHERE cfname LIKE '%mycustomfield%';
{code}
(i) Where 'mycustomfield' is your custom field name.
{quote}

